; font-size:12pt">for care </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to receive regulated financial advice so that they can make informed decisions about how best to pay for their care needs. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Background:</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="color:#333333; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">3.1</span><span style="color:#333333; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="color:#333333; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Self</span><span style="color:#333333; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">-</span><span style="color:#333333; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">funders in the current adult social care system are those who have assets (including property) of more than £23,250.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">3.2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">A substantial number of people in the care system fund all of their care (43%). A further 14% make top up payments (</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">payment o</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">f additional costs via a third party</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">)</span><a name="_ftnref2"></a><a href="#_ftn2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="color:#333333; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">3.3</span><span style="color:#333333; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="color:#333333; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">In some areas of the country, the majority of people pay for all their care costs - 55% in the South East have to pay all their care costs, 53% in the South West and 50% in the East</span><a name="_ftnref3"></a><a href="#_ftn3">[3]</a><span style="color:#333333; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="color:#333333; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="color:#333333; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">3.4</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Unfortunately there </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">is a lack of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> awareness and</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> access to appropriate regulated financial advice and no obvious place for many self</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">-</