span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">-</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">funders to be given information and advice on how to access independent financial advice. While this is a step in t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">he right direction, as recommended by the Joint Committee on the Draft Care and Support Bill</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">local autho</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">rity services should recommend financial advisers only if they are regulated by the Financial Services Authority (now the Financial Conduct Authority). </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">5.2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">As outlined in point 3.5</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, the LGiU has estimated that the cost of self funders depleting their cap</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ital and falling back on state funding costs local authorities £425 million each year in England alone. It would be worth local authorities </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">seeking to find ways to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">reduc</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> this amount, particularly given the cuts in local authority funding and the potential</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> cost to local authorities of implementing the Care Bill. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">5.3</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Although t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">he Spending Round announcement </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">(</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">June 2013</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> made provisions for £335 million to be made available to local authorities in 2015-16 so that they can prepare for reforms to the system of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> social </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">care funding, there are some doubts to whether this is enough. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">5.4</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The proposals outlined in the Care Bill are set to be implemented between 2015 and 2016, and will </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">result in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">local authorities tak</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> on a number of significant duties. Such propos</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ed new roles include the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">running of a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">D</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">eferred </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">P</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ayment </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">S</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">cheme, wh</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ich will be an interest bearing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> loan. Local authorities will </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">also </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">have to manage and calculate each individual’s care account meter which will run until they reach the cap. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">5.5</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Alongside th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">is, there will be an increase in the number of both eligibility and financial assessments that will need to be carried out. It has also been estimated that 500,000</span><a name="_ftnref6"></a><a href="#_ftn6">[6]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> more people will make contact with their local authority in order to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">start</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> their care accou</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">nt meter. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">5.6</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">This will inevitably mean that local authorities will have to put in place new IT systems, re-train staff a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">nd increase workforce capacity. All of which will mean an increase in spending. We therefore believe that local autho</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">rities should ad</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">opt</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and would benefit from</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">efficient and low cost </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ways of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">making significant</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">savings, including those</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> outlined in this response. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">November 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="color:#333333; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">Laing and Buisson 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn2"></a><a href="#_ftnref2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="color:#333333; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">Laing and Buisson 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn3"></a><a href="#_ftnref3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="color:#333333; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">Laing and Buisson 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn4"></a><a href="#_ftnref4">[4]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt"> Oliver Wyman 2009</span><a name="_GoBack"></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn5"></a><a href="#_ftnref5">[5]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt"> Independent Ageing 2013 - LGiU</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn6"></a><a href="#_ftnref6">[6]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">Caring for our future consultation – Department of Health 2013</span></p></body></html>